ce:section.ce:para:
The nanocomposite N-GQDs@Cit-HA@MIP probe was synthesized via sol-gel polymerization (
                        Fig. 1A
                        ). In a brown bottle, 8.0 mg of meclofenamic acid (template molecule) were dissolved in 5.0 mL of ethanol. Then, 48 μL of APTES (functional monomer) were added and mixed under magnetic stirring for 30 min. Next, 9.0 mg of Cit-HA were added to the mixture, and stirring continued for 10 min. Lastly, 5.0 mL of N-GQDs, 200 μL of TEOS and 200 μL of NH3 were added to the mixture solution, and stirring continued for 2 h, at which point the N-GQDs@Cit-HA@MIP nanocomposite was obtained. The template molecule was removed from the polymer layer of the synthesized nanocomposite by washing with 20.0 mL of ethanol until no template molecule could be detected in the solvent with the UV–Vis spectrophotometer. The nanocomposite N-GQDs@Cit-HA@MIP fluorescent probe was dried at room temperature. A non-imprinted polymer probe (N-GQDs@Cit-HA@NIP) was also synthesized using the same process but without the addition of meclofenamic acid.
